<br>
To complain about not having enough spell slots as a hybrid class is kind of annoying to me.  I have about 200 spells scribed in my spellbook and always have to make decisions about which spells just aren't important enough to keep memmed.  High end encounters aren't too bad just because Verant made us useless as anything but buff/debuff whores.  However in a normal exp group I am always forced to give up spells I'd like to have memmed but just can't.  Debuffs (tash/slow) + stuns (normally 2) + mezzes (1 or 2 depending on situation) + mana tap + rune or bedlam = all my spell slots.  If I only have one mez memmed then I have ONE spell slot in which to switch out the various buffs I am constantly refreshing or put dispell up in for certain mobs.  Now compare that to your life taps + snare + other dots + fd and I'd say you're not quite so pressed for spell slots.  Yes your argument goes beyond simple spell slots but it's just something that bugs me when my class has more spells than any other in the game yet is forced to use the same amount of spell slots as classes with half the number of spells.<br>
<br>
If anyone has the right to be upset about this mask it's the monks.  They have no casting time but they sure as hell have some refresh time on the FD button when they fail.  And I know that the refresh time on monk's FD is more than 1.7 seconds (the cast time you mentioned on the mask you said was instant recast).  SK's (esp troll/ogre sk's) also have it easier as far as getting more HP goes so I'd say even though trolls/ogres can't get this they certainly don't have the shortest end of the stick.  With the way verant works I'm sure we'll see the item completely nerfed before you'll see any changes to the classes that can use it. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46578"> Salta </a>
<br>Phantasmist
<br><a href="http://www.lotuscult.com">LC</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showMessage?topicID=341.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showMessage?topicID=268.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.threadControl?topicID=332.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=332.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=332.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub54.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1">General<option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm2">Role Playing<option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm3">Tricks of the Trade<option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm4">Trade/Buy/Sell<option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13">Flame Boards<option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm15">Custom Titles<option value="quelliousquaterstherebirthfrm